                <p>We provide personalized FERS annuity calculations using your actual service records, salary history, and benefit elections — accounting for every factor that affects your pension amount.</p>
                <p>The basic FERS formula is: <strong>Years of Creditable Service × High-3 Average Salary × Multiplier</strong>. For example, a federal employee with 25 years of service and a high-3 salary of $95,000 would receive an annual annuity of $23,750 using the standard 1% multiplier (25 × $95,000 × 0.01 = $23,750). However, real calculations often involve adjustments for part-time service, sick leave credit, special category provisions, and survivor benefit reductions.</p>
